1
00:00:20,359 --> 00:00:22,000
Greetings, Your Highness.

2
00:00:24,440 --> 00:00:27,280
I should apologize to you.

3
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:29,719
Due to my carelessness,

4
00:00:29,719 --> 00:00:32,479
I almost messed up your plan.

5
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:39,359
Anyway, a minister cannot keep me
from doing whatever I want.

6
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,560
Long Zhen Li Jiu.

7
00:00:49,079 --> 00:00:51,640
Racing against time
to change the nation.

8
00:00:55,039 --> 00:00:55,679
Your Highness.

9
00:00:57,520 --> 00:01:00,840
Do you have something
to say on your knees?

10
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,719
You're wise, ambitious,
and a pillar in the nation.

11
00:01:03,719 --> 00:01:05,959
And now, the nation is in peril.

12
00:01:05,959 --> 00:01:11,280
The emperor is still too young,
and urgently in need of full assistance.

13
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:18,599
I earnestly wish you to endure
for the country and the people.

14
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:23,424
You want me to me endure?
I've been doing it.

15
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:27,396
As a prince,

16
00:01:29,079 --> 00:01:32,959
I've been living without worry.

17
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:41,400
I've decided not to endure anymore
because of the country and the people.

18
00:01:42,599 --> 00:01:44,120
If I continue to endure,

19
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:52,159
the nation might be in grave danger.

20
00:01:52,799 --> 00:01:55,680
I know and admire your great cause

21
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:58,719
of developing
and strengthening the nation.

22
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:02,239
Yet, to save the nation
from going over the brink,

23
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:05,359
do you have to usurp the throne?

24
00:02:08,719 --> 00:02:11,759
If the country is so weak

25
00:02:11,759 --> 00:02:14,280
and nobody reshuffles the court,

26
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:21,984
the person sitting in the seat
might not be an Aisin-Gioro.

27
00:02:21,984 --> 00:02:27,008
Your Highness,
are you sure this is your decision?

28
00:02:27,599 --> 00:02:33,800
I'm sure, but it's not my own thing.

29
00:02:34,879 --> 00:02:38,360
You'll destroy
this 300-year-old dynasty.

30
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:43,360
Aren't you afraid of becoming a sinner
for your selfish desires?

31
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:48,080
Did I allow you to look up, minion?

32
00:02:49,879 --> 00:02:53,400
How could you know my thoughts?

33
00:02:55,759 --> 00:03:01,280
You don't know what I am thinking,
just like everyone else.

34
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:06,960
You think I want that throne?
You're wrong.

35
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:12,120
I thought about it,

36
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:16,240
but I couldn't find the right person
for the throne.

37
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,439
It's a crazy pipe dream.

38
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:27,560
I might be crazy, but it's not a dream.

39
00:04:58,436 --> 00:05:03,232
=Heroes=

40
00:05:04,196 --> 00:05:06,432
=Episode 28=

41
00:05:07,492 --> 00:05:08,224
(Saintly Wise, Beloved Homelands)

42
00:05:17,639 --> 00:05:18,279
Sir.

43
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:24,439
I just left the court
and came to tell you something.

44
00:05:27,079 --> 00:05:29,279
Are you going to Fujian tomorrow?

45
00:05:29,279 --> 00:05:31,160
I'm leaving tonight. I want to go there

46
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,120
to see if there are
any clues left behind.

47
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,720
Good. I wish you success.

48
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,600
I will do my best.

49
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,920
You have to.

50
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:44,279
Otherwise,
we'll have nothing else to do.

51
00:05:46,319 --> 00:05:50,759
After you leave the capital
for Fujian tonight.

52
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:53,879
I won't order you
to change your mission again.

53
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:58,600
If anyone gives you orders in the name
of the Imperial Household Department,

54
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,720
you must not believe it.

55
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,879
Yes, sir.

56
00:06:01,879 --> 00:06:03,920
Keep it in mind.

57
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:13,920
If anything happens to me,

58
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:16,439
and you find the Altar Treasure,

59
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:21,160
take this token
to see Prince Regent Zaifeng.

60
00:06:21,879 --> 00:06:25,759
Apart from him, you can't tell anyone
about the secret treasure.

61
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:27,800
Keep it.

62
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,399
Sir, why do you say this?

63
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:35,600
Is it because of the rebellion
on the eleventh day of the fifth month?

64
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:39,759
I've long prepared for the rebellion.
No need to worry.

65
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:43,040
I am worried about you.

66
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:45,399
The gainer of the secret treasure

67
00:06:45,399 --> 00:06:48,839
will directly determine the future
of the nation.

68
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:53,000
So you have a great burden
of responsibility.

69
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,639
Understood.

70
00:07:03,399 --> 00:07:05,199
Getai is not going with you.

71
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:10,680
He's been working for me since he was
a kid. It's been so many years.

72
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,896
Let him stay by my side this time.

73
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:14,112
Yes.

74
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:24,959
Be grateful to the pigeons flying
over the clouds.

75
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:32,480
Muqing, do you know the merits
of pigeons?

76
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,199
Pigeons know the way.

77
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:39,360
Yes, they can fly very far.

78
00:07:40,199 --> 00:07:42,199
But they will always fly back.

79
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:50,079
Remember what I have said.

80
00:07:50,079 --> 00:07:52,120
I wish you success.

81
00:08:20,839 --> 00:08:25,040
When I was young, I loved
to walk through the crowds at the fair

82
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,519
to watch the sugar-figure blowing.

83
00:08:27,519 --> 00:08:29,439
I never get tired of seeing it.

84
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:32,799
Once I told my father I wanted
to be a sugar-blower when I grew up.

85
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:34,879
Hearing that,
he kicked me out of the house.

86
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,759
Before the imperial examination,
my father told me

87
00:08:39,759 --> 00:08:43,360
if I failed, he'd kick me out
and let me be a sugar-blower.

88
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:45,440
You couldn't fail.

89
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:50,320
Being a sugar-blower is good.
I don't need to worry about anything.

90
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:53,600
Even if things change,
I still can be a sugar-blower.

91
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:56,879
Children always love to buy sugar.

92
00:08:56,879 --> 00:08:58,799
Who cares who's the ruler?

93
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:04,799
It's a pot of sugar,
simmering into syrup.

94
00:09:04,799 --> 00:09:07,879
If you like,
take a straw and swirl it inside.

95
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:09,120
And you'll get something out of it.

96
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,759
If you don't like it,
just throw it back into the pot.

97
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:14,720
In an instant,
it will melt into its original form.

98
00:09:15,519 --> 00:09:20,000
Any forms will become the same.

99
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,879
Sir, it's done.

100
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:25,879
Good.

101
00:09:28,799 --> 00:09:29,888
It looks good.

102
00:09:33,284 --> 00:09:35,919
It is truly good.

103
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,559
Sir.

104
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,639
Sir, it's too much.

105
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:45,960
Say thanks.

106
00:09:46,639 --> 00:09:48,399
Thank you, sir.

107
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,000
Lift.

108
00:10:11,039 --> 00:10:13,440
Look, green peppers.

109
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:23,120
Hot and freshly made.

110
00:10:27,279 --> 00:10:28,399
I remember you love

111
00:10:28,399 --> 00:10:31,759
to eat the mutton
from the Ma Shop in Qianmen.

112
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:36,600
You remember I love this dish.

113
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:42,240
Thick slices. It's indeed tasty. Drink.

114
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,159
You eat.

115
00:11:15,559 --> 00:11:17,360
It's getting dark.

116
00:11:22,639 --> 00:11:26,759
I have checked it over and over.
It is foolproof tonight.

117
00:11:27,639 --> 00:11:30,944
You've been with me for years. How can
you be absolutely certain of anything?

118
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:34,279
There's no foolproof thing.

119
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:40,000
I mean, everything is well prepared.

120
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,080
Wait.

121
00:11:54,879 --> 00:11:58,759
Having been working for so many years,
I've saved some money.

122
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,919
The money is all yours.

123
00:12:08,759 --> 00:12:12,879
Sir, if I succeed tonight,

124
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:17,000
my career will take off.

125
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:22,840
If not, money will mean nothing to me.

126
00:12:24,279 --> 00:12:27,320
If you fail, try to escape.

127
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,080
This money is enough
for you to live a life.

128
00:12:42,919 --> 00:12:46,240
For me, tonight, it's make or break.

129
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,200
Whether we can live or not
depends on tonight.

