- Great.
- Great.

140
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:19,360
We have utterly lost. We admit it.

141
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,328
No.

142
00:16:24,039 --> 00:16:28,679
If your assassination is successful,

143
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:32,440
it will mean you utterly fail.

144
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:39,399
I know most of you are loyal to Cunqing.

145
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,519
That's why you are willing
to risk your lives to assassinate me.

146
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:50,039
I won't reason with you. Let's talk
about the similarities and differences.

147
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:55,559
It's either me or Cunqing.

148
00:16:56,919 --> 00:17:01,408
We both agree
to make the country strong.

149
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:09,079
The difference is that Cunqing
puts the royal family first,

150
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:13,559
while I want
to weaken the imperial power.

151
00:17:14,799 --> 00:17:19,279
Cunqing wants to assassinate me
for fear I would stage a coup.

152
00:17:20,559 --> 00:17:26,319
I do want to stage a coup
because I want to change the nation.

153
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:33,920
You attempted
to kill the Prince of the First Rank.

154
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:37,000
That's already a huge crime.

155
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:42,240
Given you don't know the similarities
and differences,

156
00:17:43,079 --> 00:17:44,279
I'm giving you a choice.

157
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:51,319
Those willing to follow me can survive.
The rest can kneel and die.

158
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:02,944
(Upright and Incorrupt)

159
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,559
Where is the feather fan I gave you?

160
00:19:02,599 --> 00:19:06,359
That fan wasn't suitable for me,
so I gave it to a subordinate.

161
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,216
Who did you give it to?

162
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:13,759
Men Sandao?

163
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:15,839
Yes.

164
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:20,039
Good. Very good.

165
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:28,400
It's okay
if you refuse to seize the chance.

166
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,319
Hopefully, Men Sandao knows what to do.

167
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:35,519
Yes, as an ignorant minister,

168
00:19:35,519 --> 00:19:38,200
how dare I hinder you,
an ambitious prince?

169
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,599
You're wrong, Cunqing.

170
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:46,279
You are admirable as a minister.

171
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:53,319
You are loyal and work hard
for the imperial family.

172
00:19:53,319 --> 00:19:58,640
You even resorted to assassination
to stop me.

173
00:20:02,628 --> 00:20:03,844
You should know

174
00:20:05,504 --> 00:20:11,480
that killing the imperial family
is a grave crime.

175
00:20:12,319 --> 00:20:15,640
Success would mean saving the nation,
failure would mean its destruction.

176
00:20:16,279 --> 00:20:17,799
You're being silly and obstinate.

177
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:24,880
Even at this point,
you still can't see the situation?

178
00:20:27,079 --> 00:20:30,279
Your Highness, I understand.

179
00:20:30,279 --> 00:20:35,440
Prince Regent Zaifeng announced
he'd start constitutionalism in 1917.

180
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:38,000
Later, it was moved up to 1913.

181
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,200
Doesn't it mean that the Prince Regent
is also determined to reform?

182
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:45,720
Your Highness, I know the situation.

183
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,279
I also hope to see the nation rise again

184
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:52,119
after the pains of transformation.

185
00:20:52,119 --> 00:20:56,680
But it's not my responsibility
or mission.

186
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,960
What is your responsibility and mission?

187
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:04,480
Uphold imperial power. As the minister
of the Imperial Household Department,

188
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:08,559
upholding imperial power
is my sole responsibility and mission.

189
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,279
Upholding imperial power?

190
00:21:13,599 --> 00:21:18,359
Indeed, you are a good minister.

191
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:24,240
You have strategies,
a great vision, and means.

192
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:29,160
If you'd been born decades
or a century earlier,

193
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:32,839
you would have been an excellent talent
to assist the emperor.

194
00:21:32,839 --> 00:21:37,440
Sadly, you were born in this era.
You're short-sighted.

195
00:21:38,559 --> 00:21:40,400
You're right.

196
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:44,680
Anyway, I lost.
It's pointless to say anything.

197
00:21:46,759 --> 00:21:50,559
Do you know why you lost?

198
00:21:51,079 --> 00:21:54,759
It doesn't matter anymore.
There's no use crying over spilled milk.

199
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:02,640
Do you think I only placed Khankh
by your side?

200
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,960
You're resourceful.

201
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:14,799
I don't think
you only placed one person by my side.

202
00:22:17,519 --> 00:22:19,039
I'm taking a gamble.

203
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:22,400
Since I've come this far,
I have to take the gamble.

204
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:28,759
Those who tried to kill you tonight
are all my most trusted subordinates.

205
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:32,640
I'm afraid in your eyes,

206
00:22:33,279 --> 00:22:36,032
my trusted subordinates are a joke.

207
00:22:36,759 --> 00:22:39,759
They don't work for you

208
00:22:40,759 --> 00:22:44,920
not because I give them money
or good career prospects.

209
00:22:46,079 --> 00:22:51,328
That's because they believe
that I can turn things around.

210
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:57,759
I will not let the country fall
into the hands of others.

211
00:23:00,799 --> 00:23:06,680
I have committed a huge crime,
and I know that I will die.

212
00:23:07,799 --> 00:23:12,400
If you think
my people will trust and follow you,

213
00:23:13,359 --> 00:23:16,839
please show mercy and spare them.

214
00:23:16,839 --> 00:23:19,799
I believe they will
be even more loyal to you.

215
00:23:21,799 --> 00:23:23,200
It makes sense.

216
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:31,400
I've been thinking on my way here.

217
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:39,720
I was thinking about whether
to persuade you to follow me.

218
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:44,799
Later, I just laughed.

219
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:51,720
I laughed at my hypocrisy.

220
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:59,960
Do I have to watch you cry
and thank me for being merciful?

221
00:24:02,839 --> 00:24:08,920
You're a good minister,
so I will let you be.

222
00:24:23,264 --> 00:24:30,240
To change the nation,
we must start by changing the Qing Code.

223
00:24:31,279 --> 00:24:37,279
Cunqing, I'll spare your entire family.

224
00:24:38,559 --> 00:24:42,519
Nor will I punish anyone besides you.

225
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:49,799
Your dead body will remain intact.
I'll even let you do it yourself.

226
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,599
Please do me one last favor.

227
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:07,960
I don't dare to hope you'll give up
the rebellion, but I need your promise.

228
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:12,039
If your rebellion succeeds,

229
00:25:12,039 --> 00:25:14,880
I beg you to keep your word.

230
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:20,279
You will do all you can
to restore the prestige of the nation.

231
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:29,248
Zaifeng told me

232
00:25:30,944 --> 00:25:35,960
that it was hard and too slow
to realize constitutionalism.

233
00:25:36,599 --> 00:25:42,656
He told me to do it quicker

234
00:25:43,839 --> 00:25:47,920
and be decisive in troubled times.

235
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:57,079
Impossible, I don't believe it.

236
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:08,880
Impossible! I don't believe it!

237
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:17,248
(The first day of the fifth month, 1911,
ten days away from Grain in Ear)

238
00:26:20,420 --> 00:26:23,119
(Suzhou, Jiangsu)

239
00:26:23,119 --> 00:26:23,904
