241
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,079
Please give me some food.

242
00:26:33,279 --> 00:26:33,960
I'm hungry.

243
00:26:35,519 --> 00:26:36,880
Sir, two bowls of noodles.

244
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:37,559
Alright.

245
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:40,519
Sit.

246
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,880
Hurry and go.

247
00:26:49,799 --> 00:26:50,480
Move.

248
00:26:52,279 --> 00:26:53,056
Come here.

249
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,880
He looks like...

250
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,160
Look like a human trafficker.

251
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,039
Four coins.

252
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,104
Please offer more.

253
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:14,599
I can't. Here.

254
00:27:14,599 --> 00:27:15,240
Alright then.

255
00:27:18,079 --> 00:27:20,000
He's really a human trafficker.

256
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:22,599
Go.

257
00:27:24,319 --> 00:27:26,039
You eat here. I'll be right back.

258
00:27:34,799 --> 00:27:35,359
Hurry up.

259
00:27:42,039 --> 00:27:43,880
Sir, what's up?

260
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,480
Did you buy this child?

261
00:27:48,839 --> 00:27:49,920
Who are you, sir?

262
00:27:53,892 --> 00:27:55,232
(Constable of Dagu County)

263
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,880
So you are a constable.
I'm from the local opera troupe.

264
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:03,519
This girl's family is poor
and can't support her.

265
00:28:03,519 --> 00:28:05,440
Her mother gave her to me.

266
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:07,328
If she works hard,

267
00:28:07,328 --> 00:28:09,400
she can make a living.

268
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:12,559
She looks clever and pretty.

269
00:28:12,559 --> 00:28:14,359
She might become a leading role one day.

270
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:17,680
Her mother sold her to you
or gave her to you?

271
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:18,200
Well...

272
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:25,359
I just saw you paying.

273
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:29,680
Yes, I paid. At the agreed price.

274
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,960
I'm afraid the woman
who sold her is not her mother.

275
00:28:38,519 --> 00:28:39,480
She said she was.

276
00:28:45,599 --> 00:28:47,920
The woman who brought you here
is your mother?

277
00:28:50,519 --> 00:28:52,519
What are you afraid of?
I am a constable.

278
00:28:52,519 --> 00:28:54,279
Just tell me. Is she your mother?

279
00:28:57,079 --> 00:28:59,200
Kid, don't be scared.

280
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:09,119
Tell me. Is the person
who brought you here your mother?

281
00:29:15,759 --> 00:29:17,039
You...

282
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,119
- Move.
- Sir.

283
00:29:20,119 --> 00:29:22,799
It's a misunderstanding, sir.

284
00:29:29,759 --> 00:29:31,000
He's from an opera troupe.

285
00:29:33,319 --> 00:29:36,319
Even so, he can't buy a child.

286
00:29:37,759 --> 00:29:41,200
It's okay if they make a deal.

287
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,240
What deal?

288
00:29:42,839 --> 00:29:46,960
You know what? The person
who sold the girl is not her mother.

289
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:52,480
I know, but we
can't find the trafficker.

290
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:56,000
Come on. Have some sunflower seeds.

291
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,160
It's your job to find the trafficker.

292
00:30:05,759 --> 00:30:10,640
Listen, buddy. We both are constables.

293
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:14,119
I know what you mean.

294
00:30:14,119 --> 00:30:17,799
What can you do
even if you find the trafficker?

295
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:23,160
Look at that child. How thin she is.

296
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:27,319
Her clothes are clearly altered.
Old coarse cloth.

297
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,160
Her family can't raise her.

298
00:30:31,119 --> 00:30:32,599
To speak frankly,

299
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:37,079
many poor families sold their children.

300
00:30:37,079 --> 00:30:42,440
At best, they're sold to rich families.
At worst, some are sold to brothels.

301
00:30:43,039 --> 00:30:46,640
This girl is lucky enough
to be sold to an opera troupe.

302
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:49,799
Why do you care about such matters?

303
00:30:49,799 --> 00:30:50,912
How can I not care?

304
00:30:51,519 --> 00:30:54,160
As a constable,
I'm responsible for the people.

305
00:30:55,119 --> 00:30:57,240
Have some sunflower seeds.

306
00:30:57,240 --> 00:31:02,319
Take them away. It shouldn't be hard
for a local constable to find someone.

307
00:31:02,319 --> 00:31:04,519
Where is this child's home?
Where are her parents?

308
00:31:04,519 --> 00:31:06,160
If you want, you can find out.

309
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:09,599
If you do nothing,
the criminal will get away with this.

310
00:31:09,599 --> 00:31:11,279
Aren't you being irresponsible?

311
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:16,799
You are quite stubborn.
I can find her parents.

312
00:31:16,799 --> 00:31:19,559
But what if her family is so poor

313
00:31:19,559 --> 00:31:20,880
that they have to sell the child?

314
00:31:21,799 --> 00:31:24,519
You send the kid back home,
and then her parents sell her again.

315
00:31:24,519 --> 00:31:25,599
She might be sold to a brothel.

316
00:31:25,599 --> 00:31:28,004
Do you think you're doing a good deed?

317
00:31:28,004 --> 00:31:29,472
Parents love their kids.

318
00:31:29,472 --> 00:31:31,039
How could parents
abandon their children?

319
00:31:31,039 --> 00:31:33,359
Besides, without investigating it,
you concluded

320
00:31:33,359 --> 00:31:34,432
that the child was abandoned.

321
00:31:35,039 --> 00:31:37,880
What if her parents are looking for her
right now?

322
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:41,160
Enough, I can't make you understand.

323
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:43,160
I'll find her parents for you, alright?

324
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:44,240
You're not doing it for me.

325
00:31:45,599 --> 00:31:47,160
If not for you, for whom then?

326
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:49,640
It's your responsibility.
It's not for anyone.

327
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:53,880
Fine, I'll do it for myself, alright?

328
00:31:54,559 --> 00:31:56,119
Go. Find her parents.

329
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:58,480
Hurry up.

330
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:07,359
- How irresponsible.
- Move.

331
00:32:13,319 --> 00:32:16,519
Why can't I sell her?
Will you support us then?

332
00:32:17,759 --> 00:32:19,480
What can she do with me?

333
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,480
If I don't sell her to an opera troupe,

334
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:23,119
should she stay with me doing this?

335
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:29,079
She's my daughter and I love her,
but what can I do?

336
00:32:29,799 --> 00:32:31,359
I don't even know how to support her.

337
00:32:32,119 --> 00:32:34,440
I raised her until she was five
before sending her away.

338
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:35,759
I'm good enough to her.

339
00:32:37,319 --> 00:32:38,880
If she stays in the opera troupe,

340
00:32:39,599 --> 00:32:43,079
perhaps ten years later, she could
become a concubine in a wealthy family.

341
00:32:43,079 --> 00:32:47,240
If she stays with me, she'll end up
like me in less than ten years.

342
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:51,759
I've had enough of this life.
I don't want her to suffer any longer.

343
00:32:52,559 --> 00:32:54,440
I have to get rid of this nuisance.

344
00:32:55,119 --> 00:32:57,088
I'm the most beautiful nearby.

345
00:32:57,668 --> 00:33:00,448
But my business is the worst
because of her.

346
00:33:01,039 --> 00:33:04,359
She's too little
to mess up your business.

347
00:33:05,519 --> 00:33:09,359
Sir, how do I work with her by my side?

348
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:15,200
So you don't want me to sell her?

349
00:33:15,759 --> 00:33:17,960
Fine, I am reluctant to part with her.

350
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:22,400
You give me money. It's not costly
to support my daughter and me.

351
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:25,480
With six taels of silver a year,
my daughter and I can get by.

352
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:28,720
Give me 60 taels to raise her, okay?

353
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:47,839
Sir, come and have some fun.

354
00:34:02,079 --> 00:34:06,920
If she's sent away,
both she and I can survive.

355
00:34:07,599 --> 00:34:11,456
Otherwise, she and I
will starve to death.

356
00:34:12,119 --> 00:34:14,360
I have an illness
and can't afford the treatment.

357
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:18,144
When she grows up and wants to find me,

358
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:20,440
I fear I may already be dead.

359
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,639
Come to me again.

360
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:33,079
What's her name?

361
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:36,719
Her name is Linglong.

362
00:34:37,559 --> 00:34:38,400
What's her surname?

363
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,039
I don't know.

364
00:34:41,559 --> 00:34:42,480
What's your surname?

365
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:47,840
Mine? My surname is Shen.

366
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:51,119
(Shen Meifeng)

367
00:34:51,119 --> 00:34:55,000
Sir, come and have fun. Come on in.

368
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:57,599
Take care.

369
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:04,679
Shen Linglong, let's go.

370
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:10,239
Mr. Zhang, long time no see.

371
00:35:12,239 --> 00:35:13,239
Come and have fun.

372
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,079
Take care, sir.

373
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,440
Come on in.

374
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:32,880
Come on in. This way, please.

375
00:35:34,159 --> 00:35:36,239
I'm sorry, sir. I wronged you.

376
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:40,880
Taking disciples is allowed,
but trafficking children is not.

377
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:42,480
Yes, you're right.

378
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:43,239
Don't do it again.

379
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,679
Your name is Shen Linglong.

380
00:35:51,079 --> 00:35:53,639
Name is important.
Have you remembered it?

381
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:03,776
You must also remember
that no one can help you.

382
00:36:03,776 --> 00:36:04,996
You can only rely on yourself.

383
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:11,159
You need to become strong enough
so that no one can bully you.

384
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:17,679
Otherwise, you'll be trampled underfoot.

385
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,800
I haven't seen you cry.

386
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:26,440
It means you're strong and tough enough.

387
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:29,760
You must stay tough.

388
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:32,760
Crying will only make you weaker.

389
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:39,199
When you want to cry,
just think about what I told you.

390
00:37:19,788 --> 00:37:23,404
♪Blood refines the sword,
and wind forges the blade♪

391
00:37:23,692 --> 00:37:27,078
♪I am still that person
with rough edges♪

392
